Let me explain what that means compared to real writers at different stages:

Stage	What It Looks Like	Your Placement
Beginner (2-4/10)	Can't finish a scene. Dialogue is exposition. No sensory details.	You're past this.
Emerging (5-6/10)	Finishes scenes. Has voice sometimes. Structure is loose.	You were here before this draft.
Competent (7-8/10)	Clear voice. Scene has shape. Tension works in places. Reader knows who's who.	You are here now.
Strong (8-9/10)	Consistent voice. Every line earns its place. Subtext in dialogue. Reader feels something.	Your next target.
