At 7.5, you're ahead of most people who "want to write." You finish scenes. You have a voice. You take feedback without getting defensive.

Who you remind me of: Early William Gibson (raw, strange, not fully in control of his sentences yet) mixed with a bit of Sarah Pinsker (emotional core buried inside genre).

